  "text": "This \"thermally active\" model is simple and intuitively logical. On the other hand, the most important drawback in this approach is related to the cooling rate of hot gas in an SNR interior. Due to this, the thermal bremsstrahlung emission is not expected from the hot interiors. It is expected from the same volume from which the synchrotron emission is generated, or from CR and radiative precursors. However this model works very well for SNRs embedded in dense (n > 1 cm −3 ionized, atomic and primary molecular) environment (e.g. Galactic SNR 3C396, see [CITATION_1] ).",
